==English==
===Etymology===
The term comes from the Latin ''gluma'', meaning "husk of grain". It can also be seen in the French verb, ''glubere'' meaning "to peel".

===Noun===
'''glume''' (Plural: [[glumes]])

# A glume is a basal [[bract]] in the flowers of grasses (Poaceae) and sedges (Cyperaceae). Specifically, it is a basal, membranous, outer sterile husk or bract in grass flowers that do not stand directly at the flower base. In grasses, two glumes enclose a [[spikelet]]. In sedges, a glume subtends each flower (or several in a small cluster). 

